Thought_Process: Because the mechanism is random serial dictatorship (each parent, in random order, picks their top remaining option), your report cannot affect others’ choices or availability—only which nursery you take when it is your turn. Under RSD, truth-telling is a dominant strategy: ranking a less-preferred nursery above a more-preferred one can only cause you to pick the worse option in states where the better one is still available, and cannot increase the chance the better one is available (since availability depends only on earlier parents’ turns and their own lists). Therefore, to maximize your expected outcome and guarantee the best possible pick whenever higher options remain, you should submit your true preference order.

This is a sequential (random-serial-dictatorship) assignment: when it is my turn, I receive the highest-ranked nursery on my submitted list that is still available. My report cannot improve availability, only which available option I take. Therefore, the best strategy is to rank nurseries in my true order so that whenever I am called, I pick my most-preferred among those remaining. Any misreport could cause me to select a less-preferred nursery even when a more-preferred one is still available.
